The carrying capacity, denoted by \(\kappa\), represents the maximum number of possums the den can support. It acts as a population cap, influencing birth rates through density-dependent feedback. As the population approaches or exceeds this threshold, birth rates decrease to reflect environmental limitations like food, space, or disease pressure.
In the model, this feedback is governed by the logistic modifier:

:Model’s modifiers {#tablemodifiers}








Symbol
Modifier Name
Explanation
Formula




\(Y\)
Mortality modifier
Increases mortality with crowding (logistic function)
\( Y = \frac{1}{1 + \exp(-\rho(N_J + N_{Ad} - \kappa))} \)


\(X\)
Birth rate modifier
Reduces birth rate based on total population
\( X = 1 - Y \)



Here, \(N\) is the total population, and \(\rho\) determines how sharply the birth rate is reduced as \(N\) approaches \(\kappa\).


